body: rent control means a price is set and cannot be changed prices are designed to reflect the balance of supply and demand when supply is less than demand price goes up when supply is more than demand price goes down when you force a price for one thing to stay low despite increasing demand that causes the price of other similar things to go up so keeping numbers extremely basic let say you are a landlord and have ten units let say it costs you 10 000 to manage that building a month so you would charge 1000 month so you can cover your expenses 1000 x 10 10 000 but the government comes along and says five of those units are rent controlled you cannot charge more than 600 month for those units well if that the case then you are only collecting 8 000 month but need to cover 10 000 in expenses so what do you do you raise the rent on those those other five units by 400 so half the place pays 600 month and the other half pays 1400 month thus rent control caused a price hike
